# Codex / GitHub Copilot Instructions for BCMS

## Project
BCMS = Broadcast Content Management System. TypeScript monorepo: Fastify 5.8.5 backend + Angular 21.2.8 frontend. 10 Docker services.

## CRITICAL RULES

### 1. Prisma Audit Extension (NEVER bypass)
All writes MUST go through `apps/api/src/plugins/audit.ts` Prisma `$extends`. Never use raw SQL for INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE.

### 2. Group-Based Auth (NEVER role-based)
Keycloak `groups` claim. 11 groups: Tekyon, Transmisyon, Booking, YayınPlanlama, SystemEng, Ingest, Kurgu, MCR, PCR, Ses, StudyoSefi. SystemEng = universal access. Always use `PERMISSIONS` map from `@bcms/shared`. Never hardcode group strings.

### 3. Optimistic Locking (Schedule & Booking ONLY)
`version` field + `If-Match` header. Use `$transaction` + `updateMany` with version in WHERE clause. Increment version. If count !== 1 → 412. See `schedule.service.ts`.

### 4. Zod Validation (ALL routes)
Validate every input with Zod before Prisma. Global handler: `ZodError` → 400.

### 5. API/Worker Split (HARD)
api container = HTTP only (`BCMS_BACKGROUND_SERVICES=none`). worker container = background services. Never merge.

## ERROR HANDLING
- Zod → 400
- Prisma P2025 → 404
- Prisma P2002/P2003 → 409
- Version conflict → 412
- Auth → 401/403
- Prod unknown → 500 (hide stack)

## FRONTEND
- Angular 21 standalone + Signals-first
- `signal()` over `BehaviorSubject`
- Components < 300 lines
- `ngModel` with `[ngModelOptions]="{standalone:true}"`
- ApiService.patch(body, version) adds `If-Match` header

## SECURITY
- `SKIP_AUTH=true` blocked in prod (double guard)
- JWT RS256 + JWKS cache, validate iss + aud/azp
- Rate limit 300/min. Exempt via `config: { rateLimit: false }`
- Never log passwords/tokens

## STYLE
- Composition > inheritance
- SRP
- Functions < 30 lines
- Early returns
- Comments explain WHY
- No TODO/FIXME without docs
- No magic numbers without constants

